==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magnate
<hw>Mag"nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[F. <ets>magnat</ets>, L. (pl.)
<ets>magnates</ets>, <ets>magnati</ets>, fr. <ets>magnus</ets> great.
See <er>Master</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A person of rank; a noble
or grandee; a person of influence or distinction in any sphere; -- used
mostly of prominent business executives; <as>as, an industrial
<ex>magnate</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the nobility, or certain high officers of
state belonging to the noble estate in the national representation of
Hungary, and formerly of Poland.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magnes</ent>⟦br⟧
